            <title>[HBASE-3156] Special case distributed log splitting on fresh cluster startup</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-3156</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If the entire HBase goes down (not a graceful stop - example namenode dies) then on a subsequent restart, the HMaster can hand off the hlog splitting to the respective region servers. This would parallelize the log splitting and maintain region server hfile locality.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
